From: Xufeng Zhang <xufeng.zhang@windriver.com>
Date: Thu, 26 May 2011 10:32:19 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] powerpc: Add Kconfig support for PPC_MERGE

commit dbc1c5c250cbedccf3571597d156e581e34b2944 remove Kconfig
support for PPC_MERGE, it states:
"There are no users of PPC_MERGE in tree so we can get rid of it."
This is not true because ocf/talitos still using it, so for ocf/talitos
working, we should add this kernel config.
Another method for ocf/talitos working is modify talitos source code,
but clearly it's not proper.

Signed-off-by: Xufeng Zhang <xufeng.zhang@windriver.com>
---
 arch/powerpc/Kconfig |    3 +++
 1 files changed, 3 insertions(+), 0 deletions(-)

diff --git a/arch/powerpc/Kconfig b/arch/powerpc/Kconfig
index 95104d7..7764bcf 100644
--- a/arch/powerpc/Kconfig
+++ b/arch/powerpc/Kconfig
@@ -19,6 +19,9 @@ config WORD_SIZE
 	default 64 if PPC64
 	default 32 if !PPC64
 
+config PPC_MERGE
+        def_bool n
+
 config ARCH_PHYS_ADDR_T_64BIT
        def_bool PPC64 || PHYS_64BIT
 
